-- Las Vegas Strip Gambling Revenue Jumps 28% in July on Baccarat
-- B y   J a m e s   C a l l a n
-- 2012-09-10T14:54:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-10/las-vegas-strip-gambling-revenue-jumps-28-in-july-on-baccarat.html
Gambling revenue on the  Las Vegas 
Strip surged 28 percent to $597.5 million in July, driven by an
increase in baccarat play.  Total Nevada gaming revenue rose 17 percent to $1.01
billion in July from a year earlier, the stateâ€™s Gaming Control
Board said today in a statement. Monthly proceeds for Clark
County, which includes downtown Las Vegas as well as the Strip,
increased 21 percent to $867 million, the board said.  Strip baccarat revenue more than doubled to $190 million in
July, compared to the same period last year. Craps also gained.  MGM Resorts International (MGM) , the largest casino operator on
the Las Vegas Strip, rose 1 percent to $10.81 at 10:51 a.m. in
New York.  Wynn Resorts Ltd. (WYNN)  gained 0.3 percent to $103.01 while
 Caesars Entertainment Corp. (CZR)  fell 0.3 percent to $7.20.  To contact the reporter on this story:
